Factory walnut grips, fixed sights, and the rare vented rib. Made in Hungary by FEG. After the original Browning patents for the Browning Hi-Power (BHP) expired, the Hungarian conglomerate of FÉG developed one of the most faithful versions of the Browning design ever made in quantity outside the FN factories in Belgium and Portugal. The BHP and the FP9 are so similar that many parts are interchangeable between them, including the magazines. So, like the BHP, the Fp9 is a single action pistol. This pistol feels great in the hand – exactly like my 1981 BHP - and has a similar trigger pull. Note: the non-vented rib version of this pistol was exported as PJK-9HP/P9M models. For FTF sale in VA, buyer must be 21+ years of age and have (1) a VA driver’s license, and (2) one of the following: a concealed carry permit, LEO ID, or a copy of VA gun store invoice in buyer’s name in last year. If no IDs or invoice, can transfer at a local FFL with a quick background check. For an out-of-state sale, will arrange shipment to buyer’s FFL, at buyer’s cost. Transaction will include bill of sale. Sorry, no trades at this time. Still available if posted.

postcontent: IF THIS IS STILL LISTED, IT IS STILL FOR SALE.  I WILL CANCEL WHEN SOLD.  A nice enough 1960's project built with a Brazilian Colt Army slide, a number of GI parts and a US made frame. Someone apparently swapped the original trigger for an adjustable, but that's not a bad thing. As I understand it, in the early 1920's the US Government provided a gun plant for Brazil in Itajuba; Colt built and ran it, provided the machinery, etc. Later the Brazilians took over the plant entirely. In nice shape, seems to work fine, bore very good with minor frosting in a couple areas. Gives the appearance of not having been shot a lot and pretty well maintained.
